Spanish Stocks: Repsol, Banco Popular, BBVA, Santander Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-21T17:08:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/spanish-stocks-repsol-banco-popular-bbva-santander-move.html
Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  fell for a
second day, losing 257.6, or 2.3 percent, to 10,810.5 at the
5:30 p.m. close in Madrid. The Madrid Stock Exchange General
Index also declined 2.3 percent today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.  Banco Popular Espanol SA (POP SM) dropped for a second day,
losing 3.8 percent to 4.42 euros. Spanish banks were among the
worst performers on the IBEX 35 Index today. Banco Santander SA
(SAN SM) slid 3.3 percent to 8.96 euros. Banco Bilbao Vizcaya
Argentaria SA (BBVA SM) fell 3 percent to 9.05 euros.  Actividades de Construccion & Servicios SA (ACS SM) slid
2.2 percent to 33.02 euros. Spain’s biggest construction
company, along with  Fomento de Construcciones y Contratas SA ,
Sacyr Vallehermoso SA and  Abertis Infraestructuras SA  will be
hurt as they adapt to international accounting rules that
prevent them from freely amortizing their assets, Expansion
reported, citing the companies and people close to the matter.
FCC shares retreated 2.2 percent to 22.62 euros. Sacyr fell 1.7
percent to 7.91 euros. Abertis slumped 3.1 percent to 14.43
euros.    Repsol YPF SA  (REP SM) slumped 2.6 percent to 23.94 euros,
breaking seven days of gains. Colombia suspended contracts
awarded to Repsol and Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL CB) to explore for
oil in an archipelago in the Caribbean, Efe reported, citing a
statement from the country’s oil regulator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in  Madrid  at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net . 